    &lt;ScreenName&gt;Mrs Charlotte Campbe&lt;/ScreenName&gt;
    &lt;CommentText&gt;After many months of severe pain, Lots of medication which did not seem to help, many days where I could not walk  my doctor referred me to the muscular skeletal clinic approx 3 month wait,who referred me for a MRI scan approx 3 months then another wait to look at the scan and then  refer me to Preston Royal another 3 month wait to see a neuro surgeon my first appointment was cancelled, my second was on the 31st August.To weeks later. 
 The appointment letter said to got to the day clinic I arrived at 8.30 in good time for my    9 am appointment. The day clinic was closed but there was no notice to say so. I went to the main reception and was sent to the wrong clinic a very nice helpful nurse showed me to the correct waiting area where I then had to wait a further hour as I had missed my slot with being in the wrong place.
I finally get to see the Dr/Neuro surgeon she did not have the scan of my back. She was most unhelpful, dismissive of my condition, and extremely unsympathetic she did not listen to anything I had to say I came out of my long awaited appointment feeling distraught, upset and truly hopeless. 
 She did however tell me several times I would get Dementia, she had a scan of my brain???
I am to be referred to a pain clinic so 4 weeks later my GP has heard nothing I have contacted Preston Royal the letter has been typed but not signed and sent. The Dr/Nero surgeon is on holiday. 

I would like to say the nurse helping with the clinic was extremely helpful and caring.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
